WorldStage Newsonline– Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, former Lags State Governor has won All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential ticket for the 2023 general elections by winning 1271 votes out of  2,322 delegates. This translated to 54.74% of the total delegates. Tinubu defeated 13 other contenders to emerge the flag bearer of the party at the Special National Convention of the party in Abuja on Wednesday. The closest contender was Hon Rotimi Amaechi who pulled 316 followed by the Vice President, Prof Yemi Osinbajo who got 235 votes. Result: Ashiwaju Ahmed Bola Tinubu 1271 Ahmed Lawan 152 Senator Ben Ayade 37 Ikeobasi Mokelu 0 Yemi Osinbajo 235 Dave Umahi 38 Tunde Bakare 0 Ahmed Sani 4 Rotimi Amaechi 316 Yahaya Bello 47 Rochas Okorocha 0 Ogbonnaya Onu 1 Void 13